ult="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 343</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>very tragical m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he's all my exercise, my m., my matter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.166" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 166</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll use you for my m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 49</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 49</bibl> <cit><quote>to give a kingdom for a m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 4, 18</bibl></cit>.
